Gather the required materials. Use PPE as shown Use only high speed disperser with agitator drum
Verify that the vessel is clean and grounded.
Ensure the drums is secured via strap to mixer (see picture)
Charge vessel with Methyl Ethyl Ketone- use only grounded metal pails
Slowly add Xylene via grounded pail
Start Agitation to approx 800 digital readout
Mix MEK and Xylene for 5 minutes
Cover the drum to prevent evaporation
Increase mixer to 1200 rpm and grind 50 minutes
After mixing bring a sample to lab, vinyl should be completely dissolved
Using grounded pail add Talc, product should be creamy gray
Add Black Tint Paste (make sure its uniform, or mix if separated
Let mix approx. 2  hours at level 1200
Using grounded pail add Acetone (Product will be hot)
After Acetone reduce mixer to 950-1000 digital readout
After 5 minutes use dedicated scoop to sample blend
Sample blend; label sample container; and deliver sample to QC Lab.
If viscosity needs adjustment lab will inform how much MEK is needed
Sample blend; label sample container; and deliver sample to QC Lab.

Clean mixer and flush pump thoroughly with MEK
